      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Not much went the way of DANGEROUS (1) from the back row in round one but he gets a golden opportunity from the ace draw tonight. Had trialled impressively going into the series and if he can show the same sort of speed here he'll be be hard to catch. BAY OF BISCAY (11) finished strongly for a nice win in the first round of heats last week, taking his record at this distance to three wins and a placing from four tries. Tougher task from the back row but he did come from there to score in Victoria three back. FIGHTER COMMAND (2) did a great job to come from the back row and win when resuming last week, his fifth success from six attempts at this distance range. Has won three of five when second-up so should be improved and a good draw could see him strike again. NYACK (4) got within 2.2m of Leap To Fame when runner-up last week and draws closer to the pegs so could go one better. Tricky draw for WAR DAN BUDDY (10) but he possesses a strong sprint so watch for him late.",
